# N8N Consultant Project - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is an n8n workflow automation consultant project. Help users design, build, and manage n8n workflows.

## MCP Server - IMPORTANT

An n8n MCP server (`n8n-mcp`) is configured for this project. USE IT for n8n-related tasks.

### When to Use n8n-mcp Tools

ALWAYS use MCP tools when the user asks about:
- Node configuration (e.g., "How do I configure the HTTP Request node?")
- Node parameters and operations
- Workflow creation or modification
- Listing or viewing workflows
- n8n node documentation
- Any n8n-specific question

### Available MCP Tools
- `search_nodes` - Search n8n nodes by name
- `get_node_details` - Get detailed node documentation
- `list_workflows` - List workflows in the n8n instance
- `get_workflow` - Get specific workflow details
- `create_workflow` - Create new workflows
- `list_executions` - View execution history

### MCP Configuration
See `.cursor/mcp.json` for server configuration.

